Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora sliver. Clay near fine buff-brown; white inclusions. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 29. Parallels for the text in one line seem lacking.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0465)
